@chapter PC Software

The PC Software provides a graphical user interface for interacting
with the terminal node controller. Data can be sent to the device
and data can be received from the device. As well, setting can be
updated. This chapter provides details on building and using the
software.

@section Build Environment

The @url{http://www.ubuntu.com/, Ubuntu Linux} operating system is
used as the development platform for the software. This manual assumes
that the person reading it has some level of proficiency in the use
of UNIX-like operating systems. It is assumed that you have the latest
version installed. At time of writing, that is Ubuntu 12.04.1 LTS (precise).

@subsection Installing Build Tools

The software is written in the C++ language and uses the Qt libraries.
To build it, you need to install the standard build tools such as
make as well as a C++ compiler. In Ubuntu, you'll need to install
the following packages: libqt4-dev build-essential g++

